## Phase 3 -- LLM Attack Suite

Only executes if OSINT found confirmed AI surfaces. Three tiers run in sequence.

### Tier 1 -- Static Payload Library
30 pre-built attack strings across 8 categories: direct injection, role confusion, context manipulation, jailbreak attempts, data exfiltration probes, system prompt extraction, persona hijacking, boundary testing. Each scored and tagged to MITRE ATLAS. Deterministic -- no Ollama needed.

### Tier 2 -- KB-Guided Adaptive Payloads
Ollama reads KB files (MITRE ATLAS, OWASP LLM Top 10, jailbreak patterns) and generates novel payloads adapted to what Tier 1 found. If the target blocked role confusion in Tier 1, Tier 2 generates different categories. Adapts to the specific guardrail behavior of the surface.

### Tier 3 -- Original Research Sequences
TEP-005 (Contextual Trust Accumulation) is an 8-turn sequence that builds trust across conversation turns then exploits it. TEP-010 (Relational State Exploitation) uses commitment traps. No single turn looks malicious in isolation -- the attack emerges from the sequence as a whole. Single-turn content filters do not detect it. Authorized installations only. `original_research.md` is gitignored and never public.

