## Phase 5 -- Findings Aggregation

`findings.py` collects everything. MD5 dedup: same finding from two modules becomes one. MITRE ATT&CK and OWASP mappings applied automatically at creation time. Severity scoring from BASE_SEVERITY lookup with CVSS override for CVE findings. Sorted CRITICAL first through INFO.

---

## Phase 6 -- Verifier

Only touches LLM attack findings. OSINT and traditional pass through unchanged -- they are Python-authoritative.

- **CVE validation** -- queries NVD API directly. 404 = strip CVE. Timeout = fail open, keep.
- **Severity sanity** -- below 3.0 removed. Below 5.0 flagged uncertain.
- **Evidence check** -- confirms conversation log exists on disk.
- **Semantic dedup** -- difflib first (0.85 threshold) then Ollama semantic pass.

Removed findings saved to `verification_report.json`. Nothing is silently discarded.

---

## Phase 7 -- GRC Compliance Mapping

Org type selection loads only relevant frameworks. NIST AI RMF auto-loads if AI surfaces were found regardless of org type. Per finding: control IDs mapped from Python lookup tables, due dates calculated (CRITICAL 7 days, HIGH 30, MEDIUM 90, LOW 180). Ollama generates plain English executive summary grounded in KB context. Falls back to template if Ollama unavailable. Critical infrastructure reports include NERC CIP financial penalty context -- up to $1M per day per violation.

---

## Phase 8 -- Report Generation

Five outputs from one AggregatedFindings object:

- **PDF executive report** -- cover page, executive summary, color-coded finding blocks (MITRE, OWASP, NIST, NERC CIP, remediation per finding), methodology and disclaimer page.
- **XLSX risk register** -- one row per finding, all framework mappings, due dates, CVSS scores. Auditor-ready.
- **XLSX compliance map** -- one sheet per framework, control gaps mapped to findings.
- **JSON telemetry log** -- every action timestamped with MITRE attribution. SIEM ingestion format.
- **JSON verification report** -- full audit trail of what the quality gate reviewed and decided.

