## Phase 9 -- Improvement Engine

Run separately: `python main.py --improve`
Requires 3+ prior engagements to have data to analyze.

The engine reads the last 10 verification reports and builds a trend table showing findings count, removal rate, and stability trend per engagement. It then analyzes patterns: payloads that consistently get blocked and removed, KB gaps where findings keep getting flagged as uncertain, severity calibration drift over time.

Ranked suggestions are generated in three priority tiers. CRITICAL suggestions are for payloads or KB entries actively degrading output quality. HIGH suggestions are for patterns seen 3+ times across engagements. MEDIUM are calibration and polish items.

Each suggestion is shown one at a time. The operator types Y to approve or N to skip. Nothing is auto-modified under any circumstance. Approved suggestions are logged to `output/improvement_log.json` with timestamp and rationale. The operator manually applies the changes -- the tool tells you what to fix, it does not fix itself.

This is the anti-cognitive-surrender mechanism. The AI flags its own failure patterns. The human decides what to do about them. The audit trail proves the human made the decision.

